      "resolution_level": 5,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_innate_immunity",
      "content": {
        "title": "C5a and C3a Anaphylatoxins",
        "definition": "Complement cleavage fragments C3a and C5a that act as chemotactic and pro-inflammatory mediators promoting mast cell degranulation and neutrophil recruitment.",
        "summary": "Anaphylatoxins link complement activation to rapid inflammatory cell influx. C5a is among the most potent neutrophil chemoattractants in acute inflammation."
      },
