      "content": {
        "title": "MAC (C5b-9) and Cell Lysis",
        "definition": "Terminal complement assembly of C5b-9 forming a membrane attack complex that inserts into target membranes and causes osmotic lysis of susceptible microbes.",
        "summary": "MAC provides direct bactericidal activity especially against Neisseria. Defects in terminal complement components increase risk of recurrent meningococcal infection."
